# Accepted vulnerabilities.
#
# Every entry here must include:
#   - CVE ID
#   - Which image it affects
#   - Why it is not exploitable in our code paths
#   - An expiration date (`exp:YYYY-MM-DD`) so Trivy re-raises the
#     finding if we forget to revisit it
#
# Before adding a line here, try to fix the vulnerability first — pin a
# newer base image, upgrade a dependency, or swap to a different runtime.
# This file is a last resort for upstream issues that are genuinely not
# exploitable in our context.

# CVE-2026-28390 — OpenSSL NULL pointer dereference DoS via crafted
# Cryptographic Message Syntax (CMS / PKCS#7) structures.
#
# Affects: strait-app runtime image (gcr.io/distroless/nodejs22-debian12)
# via libssl3 3.0.18-1~deb12u2. Fixed upstream in libssl3
# 3.0.19-1~deb12u2 and awaiting rebuild of the Google distroless image.
#
# Strait App is not exploitable: the Node runtime uses libssl only for
# TLS client connections (outbound HTTPS to the Strait API, Resend,
# Stripe, etc.) and the built-in `fetch` for the healthcheck. None of
# those code paths parse CMS. Better Auth signs JWTs via `jose`, which
# does not link against libssl. The Go `strait` image escapes this CVE
# family entirely by using distroless/static-debian12 (no libssl at
# all), which Node cannot do because Node links libssl dynamically.
#
# Reassess on or before the expiration date. If the distroless rebuild
# has landed by then, remove this line. Expiry is aligned with the four
# sibling libssl3 CVEs below, since all five ship together in the same
# Debian 12 source-package rebuild.
CVE-2026-28390 exp:2026-06-10

# CVE-2026-28387 / CVE-2026-28388 / CVE-2026-28389 / CVE-2026-31789 —
# additional libssl3 vulnerabilities in the same Debian 12 source
# package as CVE-2026-28390 above. All four are fixed upstream in
# libssl3 3.0.19-1~deb12u2 and ship together once Google rebuilds the
# distroless nodejs22-debian12 image.
#
# Affects: strait-app runtime image (gcr.io/distroless/nodejs22-debian12).
#
# Exploitability mirrors CVE-2026-28390: the Node runtime only links
# libssl for outbound TLS to trusted endpoints (Strait API, Resend,
# Stripe) and the built-in `fetch` healthcheck. None of those code paths
# parse CMS / PKCS#7 structures or accept attacker-controlled X.509
# inputs. CVE-2026-31789 is additionally a 32-bit-only heap overflow;
# our runner and image are 64-bit. The Go strait images are unaffected
# (distroless/static-debian12 ships no libssl).
#
# Reassess on or before the expiration date and remove these once the
# distroless rebuild lands.
CVE-2026-28387 exp:2026-06-10
CVE-2026-28388 exp:2026-06-10
CVE-2026-28389 exp:2026-06-10
CVE-2026-31789 exp:2026-06-10

# CVE-2026-29181 — OpenTelemetry-Go multi-value `baggage` header
# extraction triggers excessive allocations (DoS amplification).
# Fixed upstream in go.opentelemetry.io/otel 1.41.0.
#
# Affects: the bundled `soci` binary (awslabs/soci-snapshotter v0.13.0,
# the current latest release as of this pin) inside the community and
# cloud strait images. The strait binary itself ships otel >=1.41 and
# is clean.
#
# Not exploitable in our context: the soci binary is shipped for use by
# the host containerd snapshotter on nodes that pull strait images; it
# is never invoked from inside the running strait container (ENTRYPOINT
# is `strait`). Even when run on a node, soci's OTel exporter consumes
# spans it generates itself, never untrusted remote `baggage` headers.
#
# Reassess once awslabs/soci-snapshotter cuts a release newer than
# v0.13.0 that bumps go.opentelemetry.io/otel.
CVE-2026-29181 exp:2026-08-10

# CVE-2026-32280 / CVE-2026-32281 / CVE-2026-32283 — Go standard
# library TLS / x509 denial-of-service vulnerabilities. Fixed upstream
# in Go 1.25.9 and 1.26.2.
#
# Affects: the bundled `soci` binary (awslabs/soci-snapshotter v0.13.0)
# inside the community and cloud strait images. Soci v0.13.0 was built
# with Go 1.25.8; no newer soci release exists yet.
#
# Not exploitable in our context: the strait container never executes
# soci (ENTRYPOINT is `strait`, the strait binary itself is built with
# Go 1.26.x and is clean). When soci runs on a node it talks TLS only
# to ECR endpoints under AWS's control, not to attacker-supplied hosts,
# so the DoS path requires an attacker who already controls the
# registry the node is configured to pull from.
#
# Reassess once awslabs/soci-snapshotter cuts a release newer than
# v0.13.0 built with Go >=1.26.2.
CVE-2026-32280 exp:2026-08-10
CVE-2026-32281 exp:2026-08-10
CVE-2026-32283 exp:2026-08-10

# CVE-2026-46680 — containerd user-ID handling bypass that can defeat a
# `runAsNonRoot` security-context constraint. Fixed upstream in
# containerd 1.7.32.
#
# Affects: the bundled `soci` binary (awslabs/soci-snapshotter v0.13.0,
# still the latest release at this pin) inside the community and cloud
# strait images. Soci v0.13.0 statically links containerd v1.7.30; the
# strait binary itself does not link containerd and is clean.
#
# Not exploitable in our context: the strait container never executes
# soci (ENTRYPOINT is `strait`). The vulnerable containerd code path is
# the snapshotter/runtime user-ID resolution that runs on a node when
# containerd itself launches a container — it is not reachable by running
# the soci CLI, and nothing inside the strait container invokes it. Image
# `runAsNonRoot` enforcement is performed by the host kubelet/containerd,
# not by the copy of containerd vendored into soci.
#
# Reassess once awslabs/soci-snapshotter cuts a release newer than
# v0.13.0 that bumps containerd to >=1.7.32.
CVE-2026-46680 exp:2026-08-10
